# highlight-compiler

## configuration file

```bash
$ cat hl.conf
```
```
#tab separated values
#regexp colorname
INFO    blue
DEBUG   green
WARNING yellow
CRITICAL        red
^(o|l).*(Bear|Crocodile)$       magenta
```

## compile the highlighter based on the configuration file

```bash
$ ./hlcompiler.awk hl.conf > highlight.awk
$ cat highlight.awk
```

```awk
#!/usr/bin/awk -f
/INFO/ {
	printf "\033[34m%s\033[0m\n", $0; next}
/DEBUG/ {
	printf "\033[32m%s\033[0m\n", $0; next}
/WARNING/ {
	printf "\033[33m%s\033[0m\n", $0; next}
/CRITICAL/ {
	printf "\033[31m%s\033[0m\n", $0; next}
/^(o|l).*(Bear|Crocodile)$/ {
	printf "\033[35m%s\033[0m\n", $0; next}
{print $0}

```

## pipe the output of any command to the highlighter

```bash
$ head -n 15 example.log | ./highlight.awk
```
